{"title":"Claude设计负责人 | 传统设计流程已失效","slug":"drnmpgt29mu0dikx","summary":"Youtube 链接： https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo 这期播客访谈了 Claude（Anthropic）的设计负责人 Jenny Wen（前 Figma 设计总监）。在长达一个多小时的对话中，她深刻剖析了 AI 时代产品设","category":"🎙AI设计访谈合集","tags":["📂资源合集","🎙AI设计访谈合集"],"featured":false,"order":8,"level":2,"updatedAt":"2026-03-02","wordCount":1930,"sourceUrl":"https://www.yuque.com/abyssalsailor/yg90qa/drnmpgt29mu0dikx","html":"<p data-lake-id=\"ubf99c62a\" id=\"ubf99c62a\"><card type=\"inline\" name=\"image\" value=\"data:%7B%22src%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.nlark.com%2Fyuque%2F0%2F2026%2Fpng%2F1206632%2F1772461614592-ad027971-7457-4a01-a0a8-75d77308b3fd.png%22%2C%22taskId%22%3A%22u89305fb6-b7d4-4b41-8e30-9b35dccf22b%22%2C%22clientId%22%3A%22u45d04478-1051-4%22%2C%22originalType%22%3A%22binary%22%2C%22width%22%3A640%2C%22height%22%3A360%2C%22linkTarget%22%3A%22_blank%22%2C%22name%22%3A%22image.png%22%2C%22size%22%3A1278914%2C%22from%22%3A%22paste%22%2C%22originWidth%22%3A1280%2C%22originHeight%22%3A720%2C%22ratio%22%3A2%2C%22status%22%3A%22done%22%2C%22style%22%3A%22none%22%2C%22search%22%3A%22%5C%22DON'T%20TRUST%20THE%20DESIGN%20PROCESS%20JENNY%20WEN%20CLAUDE%20DESIGN%20LEAD%20FOR%20CLAUDE%22%2C%22ocrLocations%22%3A%5B%7B%22x%22%3A55%2C%22y%22%3A84%2C%22width%22%3A597%2C%22height%22%3A101%2C%22text%22%3A%22%5C%22DON'T%20TRUST%22%7D%2C%7B%22x%22%3A55%2C%22y%22%3A238%2C%22width%22%3A558%2C%22height%22%3A112%2C%22text%22%3A%22THE%20DESIGN%22%7D%2C%7B%22x%22%3A56%2C%22y%22%3A403%2C%22width%22%3A426%2C%22height%22%3A91%2C%22text%22%3A%22PROCESS%22%7D%2C%7B%22x%22%3A51%2C%22y%22%3A565%2C%22width%22%3A256%2C%22height%22%3A52%2C%22text%22%3A%22JENNY%20WEN%22%7D%2C%7B%22x%22%3A787%2C%22y%22%3A572%2C%22width%22%3A372%2C%22height%22%3A91%2C%22text%22%3A%22CLAUDE%22%7D%2C%7B%22x%22%3A49%2C%22y%22%3A627%2C%22width%22%3A393%2C%22height%22%3A41%2C%22text%22%3A%22DESIGN%20LEAD%20FOR%20CLAUDE%22%7D%5D%2C%22showTitle%22%3Afalse%2C%22title%22%3A%22%22%2C%22rotation%22%3A0%2C%22crop%22%3A%5B0%2C0%2C1%2C1%5D%2C%22averageHue%22%3A%22%23cea688%22%2C%22__spacing%22%3A%22both%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22u55a1206c%22%2C%22margin%22%3A%7B%22top%22%3Atrue%2C%22bottom%22%3Atrue%7D%7D\"></card></p><p data-lake-id=\"u034ffe66\" id=\"u034ffe66\"><span data-lake-id=\"u85236459\" id=\"u85236459\">Youtube 链接：</span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"u5b613389\" id=\"u5b613389\"><span data-lake-id=\"ua9bd1378\" id=\"ua9bd1378\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo</span></a></p><p data-lake-id=\"uc78d1343\" id=\"uc78d1343\"><span data-lake-id=\"u18865cf0\" id=\"u18865cf0\">这期播客访谈了 Claude（Anthropic）的设计负责人 Jenny Wen（前 Figma 设计总监）。在长达一个多小时的对话中，她深刻剖析了 AI 时代产品设计流程的颠覆性变化，以及设计师角色、技能树和思维方式的全面重塑。</span></p><p data-lake-id=\"u07d2dffc\" id=\"u07d2dffc\"><span data-lake-id=\"u765a0841\" id=\"u765a0841\">以下是专为</span><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u7a8c27fd\" id=\"u7a8c27fd\">产品设计师</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u675aa4f8\" id=\"u675aa4f8\">视角整理的核心观点总结与重点分类：</span></p><h3 data-lake-id=\"b7a2da4e\" id=\"b7a2da4e\"><span data-lake-id=\"uf6c0a581\" id=\"uf6c0a581\">1. 传统设计流程的消亡 (The Death of Traditional Design Process)</span></h3><p data-lake-id=\"ufe7865e8\" id=\"ufe7865e8\"><span data-lake-id=\"u0950f27d\" id=\"u0950f27d\">在过去，设计师视“发现-发散-收敛-做高保真原型”的瀑布式或双钻模型为圭臬，但在工程开发速度被 AI 极大加速的今天，这种按部就班的流程已经失效。</span></p><ul list=\"ue67fd723\"><li fid=\"ud12a36d1\" data-lake-id=\"u96165126\" id=\"u96165126\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"uceeb5e59\" id=\"uceeb5e59\">核心观点</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ud930d2aa\" id=\"ud930d2aa\">：AI 编程助手（如 Claude Code）让工程师可以瞬间做出七八个功能原型，设计师已经没有时间去精雕细琢完美的视觉稿。强行要求走完传统设计流程只会阻碍团队前进，设计师应该“放手让工程师去干（let them cook）”。</span></li><li fid=\"ud12a36d1\" data-lake-id=\"u927e1be6\" id=\"u927e1be6\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"ue3e3bd7d\" id=\"ue3e3bd7d\">设计师启示</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u224fce07\" id=\"u224fce07\">：放弃对“完美静态原型”的执念。由于大模型本身是非确定性的（Non-deterministic），很多场景根本无法在设计软件里穷举，必须基于真实的模型和代码去测试和感受。</span></li><li fid=\"ud12a36d1\" data-lake-id=\"ud06d3c1e\" id=\"ud06d3c1e\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u37af71ac\" id=\"u37af71ac\">引用原文</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u614b94ed\" id=\"u614b94ed\">：&quot;this design process that designers have been taught we sort of treat it as gospel that's basically dead&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=333\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"u0cf52ac5\" id=\"u0cf52ac5\"><span data-lake-id=\"u1d7a3333\" id=\"u1d7a3333\">05:33</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"u8608cedf\" id=\"u8608cedf\">] / &quot;you're better off not blocking that letting them cook&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=541\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"ubdf39839\" id=\"ubdf39839\"><span data-lake-id=\"ubf0f4ceb\" id=\"ubf0f4ceb\">09:01</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"uc6e7803b\" id=\"uc6e7803b\">]</span></li></ul><h3 data-lake-id=\"780c40d6\" id=\"780c40d6\"><span data-lake-id=\"uc0dd1731\" id=\"uc0dd1731\">2. 设计师的时间分配与核心职责重塑 (Shift in Time Allocation &amp; Role)</span></h3><p data-lake-id=\"uebf5e9e1\" id=\"uebf5e9e1\"><span data-lake-id=\"u031debdd\" id=\"u031debdd\">既然不用再画那么多高保真图，设计师的时间去哪了？Jenny 指出设计工作正在两极化：一方面是极其细颗粒度的“辅助执行”，另一方面是更高维度的“指引愿景”。</span></p><ul list=\"u31e50df5\"><li fid=\"u445d79db\" data-lake-id=\"u7bc24a1e\" id=\"u7bc24a1e\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"ua065da65\" id=\"ua065da65\">核心观点</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"uea5d2649\" id=\"uea5d2649\">：几年前，设计师 60%-70% 的时间在画原型；现在这部分只占 30%-40%。新增的大量时间用于与工程师结对工作（Jamming/Pairing），甚至直接在 IDE（代码编辑器）里调整代码来完成产品上线的“最后一公里”。同时，长期的设计愿景（2-5年）缩短为了 3-6 个月的快速原型指引。</span></li><li fid=\"u445d79db\" data-lake-id=\"u3add9acf\" id=\"u3add9acf\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u0906a874\" id=\"u0906a874\">设计师启示</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"uea164b6b\" id=\"uea164b6b\">：设计师必须深入到“执行层”和“实现层”。不要满足于把设计稿丢给开发，要学会直接在前端代码（如CSS/HTML）中做最后的设计打磨。</span></li><li fid=\"u445d79db\" data-lake-id=\"u52de8b5b\" id=\"u52de8b5b\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u9c080099\" id=\"u9c080099\">引用原文</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ud4293a57\" id=\"ud4293a57\">：&quot;a few years ago 60 to 70% of it was mocking and prototyping... but now I feel the mocking up part of it is 30 to 40%... and there's like a slice of it that is now like implementation as well like actually building and shipping&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=1087\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"ua12048f7\" id=\"ua12048f7\"><span data-lake-id=\"u43dcfe2c\" id=\"u43dcfe2c\">18:07</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"u30160cbc\" id=\"u30160cbc\">]</span></li></ul><h3 data-lake-id=\"8c7cf842\" id=\"8c7cf842\"><span data-lake-id=\"u9bb66ad2\" id=\"u9bb66ad2\">3. AI时代的独特竞争力：品味与“拍板” (Taste, Judgment &amp; Accountability)</span></h3><p data-lake-id=\"u1bd96141\" id=\"u1bd96141\"><span data-lake-id=\"u1f8a1af9\" id=\"u1f8a1af9\">随着 AI 写代码、生成 UI 甚至提供交互方案的能力越来越强，人类大脑的价值究竟在哪？</span></p><ul list=\"u7f307089\"><li fid=\"u524d16d6\" data-lake-id=\"u1588bf0b\" id=\"u1588bf0b\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"ucce7bd68\" id=\"ucce7bd68\">核心观点</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"uf62c04ae\" id=\"uf62c04ae\">：AI 的审美和品味确实会越来越好，甚至会给出大量优质方案。但真正困难的往往不是“如何做”，而是“做哪个”。在面对复杂分歧时，决定到底要上线什么功能、什么才是真正有意义的，并且</span><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u5e22b433\" id=\"u5e22b433\">为这个决定承担责任</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u01e12747\" id=\"u01e12747\">，依然是人类设计师/PM的绝对领域。</span></li><li fid=\"u524d16d6\" data-lake-id=\"u2833a023\" id=\"u2833a023\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u1bfe2ceb\" id=\"u1bfe2ceb\">设计师启示</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ua47160dc\" id=\"ua47160dc\">：提升自身的“产品判断力（Judgment）”和“决断力”，成为为产品结果担责的人，而非单纯的方案输出机器。</span></li><li fid=\"u524d16d6\" data-lake-id=\"uc3e8c661\" id=\"uc3e8c661\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u2d540d20\" id=\"u2d540d20\">引用原文</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ua12208f1\" id=\"ua12208f1\">：&quot;i think it will get better at taste and judgment and design... at the end of the day someone has to decide what is actually going to get built and what actually matters someone still needs to be accountable for the decision&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=1711\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"ud6ee7989\" id=\"ud6ee7989\"><span data-lake-id=\"u5edef2f0\" id=\"u5edef2f0\">28:31</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"ue9bddc93\" id=\"ue9bddc93\">]</span></li></ul><h3 data-lake-id=\"7cacbba8\" id=\"7cacbba8\"><span data-lake-id=\"uc524d847\" id=\"uc524d847\">4. 速度即信任：发布残缺但真实的产品 (Building Trust Through Speed)</span></h3><ul list=\"u637f690d\"><li fid=\"u6516d792\" data-lake-id=\"u1c374f89\" id=\"u1c374f89\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u4f621027\" id=\"u4f621027\">核心观点</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u799b5bf4\" id=\"u799b5bf4\">：Anthropic 团队在发布 Claude Co-work 等产品时，并不追求首发时的完美，而是大胆打上“研究预览（Research Preview）”的标签推向市场。信任的建立不在于首发没有 Bug，而在于你能在极短时间内听取用户反馈并火速修复更新。</span></li><li fid=\"u6516d792\" data-lake-id=\"u5e4524cd\" id=\"u5e4524cd\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u93dbf2d7\" id=\"u93dbf2d7\">设计师启示</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u5ea52cdc\" id=\"u5ea52cdc\">：在 AI 这个日新月异的领域，真实场景的数据比闭门造车的推演重要百倍。敢于用半成品试错，通过超快迭代速度来赢取用户信任。</span></li><li fid=\"u6516d792\" data-lake-id=\"u9e6d12bb\" id=\"u9e6d12bb\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u38cca244\" id=\"u38cca244\">引用原文</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ue2df1d52\" id=\"ue2df1d52\">：&quot;the promise you sort of have to make your users is is like hey we're going to put it out there but we're going to iterate... I think the way that you really lose trust around quality and releasing something early is if you release it early and then nothing ever happens&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=1563\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"ufa404a96\" id=\"ufa404a96\"><span data-lake-id=\"u6ddcae80\" id=\"u6ddcae80\">26:03</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"u42bde233\" id=\"u42bde233\">]</span></li></ul><h3 data-lake-id=\"be75f915\" id=\"be75f915\"><span data-lake-id=\"u5fd58846\" id=\"u5fd58846\">5. 极具竞争力的三类设计人才 (Three Archetypes of Future Designers)</span></h3><p data-lake-id=\"u38bb1684\" id=\"u38bb1684\"><span data-lake-id=\"u0039cb76\" id=\"u0039cb76\">当被问及现在倾向于招募什么样的人才时，Jenny 提到了在拥抱变化（Resilience）的基础上，三种最吃香的设计师画像：</span></p><ul list=\"u558b1de0\"><li fid=\"u814517e8\" data-lake-id=\"u5ff88af0\" id=\"u5ff88af0\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u3a6b14dd\" id=\"u3a6b14dd\">多面手（Strong Generalists / Block-shaped）</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u126a63fa\" id=\"u126a63fa\">：拥有极宽的技能栈（设计、工程、产品），且每一项核心技能都能达到 80 分位以上，能无缝适应边界模糊的新型团队。</span></li><li fid=\"u814517e8\" data-lake-id=\"u5c3d5af6\" id=\"u5c3d5af6\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u9ffaf19a\" id=\"u9ffaf19a\">深度专家（Deep Specialists）</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ufeef2215\" id=\"ufeef2215\">：在极细分的领域（如纯粹的顶级视觉塑造、或精通极复杂技术前端交互）达到行业前 10% 的水准，具有不可替代的辨识度。</span></li><li fid=\"u814517e8\" data-lake-id=\"u8b899d1e\" id=\"u8b899d1e\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u6e026848\" id=\"u6e026848\">硬核极客新人（Craft New Grad）</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u3d815307\" id=\"u3d815307\">：经验尚浅但不被传统大厂流程毒害的年轻人，充满谦逊与求知欲，善于直接使用最新 AI 工具构建真实项目（Build stuff），执行力极强。</span></li><li fid=\"u814517e8\" data-lake-id=\"u437aa9d3\" id=\"u437aa9d3\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u02c0fe1f\" id=\"u02c0fe1f\">引用原文</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ua75d8708\" id=\"ua75d8708\">：&quot;there's probably three archetypes of folks that are really interesting to me right now... strong generalists... a deep specialist... and my last one is probably the one that I think we're all overlooking which is what I call the craft new grad&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=2814\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"u05062c63\" id=\"u05062c63\"><span data-lake-id=\"ubb0d4c87\" id=\"ubb0d4c87\">46:54</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"u876cdb6c\" id=\"u876cdb6c\">]</span></li></ul><h3 data-lake-id=\"00d326c9\" id=\"00d326c9\"><span data-lake-id=\"u44c52349\" id=\"u44c52349\">6. 像风险投资家一样做设计：可读性框架 (The Legibility Framework)</span></h3><ul list=\"uf94229ba\"><li fid=\"ud6855b3e\" data-lake-id=\"uf3e315a1\" id=\"uf3e315a1\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u9366889c\" id=\"u9366889c\">核心观点</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"ud79fd506\" id=\"ud79fd506\">：Jenny 借用了 VC 圈的框架——如果一个想法非常清晰易懂（Legible），那它多半缺乏创新，早就被人做了。真正的机会往往藏在那些“不可读（Illegible）”的创意里：比如团队内部工程师搞出的一个看起来很乱、你一开始也看不懂，但却充满活力的复杂技术原型。</span></li><li fid=\"ud6855b3e\" data-lake-id=\"uc75f10ea\" id=\"uc75f10ea\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u40396238\" id=\"u40396238\">设计师启示</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u8aaaded1\" id=\"u8aaaded1\">：设计师应该像风投一样，敏锐地嗅出团队内那些处于萌芽状态的前沿粗糙技术。你的任务是发掘它们，并通过卓越的用户体验（UX）和故事叙述，将“不可读”的技术转化为“可读”的主流产品。</span></li><li fid=\"ud6855b3e\" data-lake-id=\"u80fa5f82\" id=\"u80fa5f82\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u8b5244d7\" id=\"u8b5244d7\">引用原文</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u7cf4dfc8\" id=\"u7cf4dfc8\">：&quot;part of the role of the designer at least... is kind of spotting the ideas that are illegible and trying to understand what's there and how to take that and like transform it whether it's through storytelling or whether it's through like the actual UX&quot; [</span><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eh8bcBIAAFo&amp;t=3199\" target=\"_blank\" data-lake-id=\"u0daac433\" id=\"u0daac433\"><span data-lake-id=\"uedafa5d7\" id=\"uedafa5d7\">53:19</span></a><span data-lake-id=\"u2ee8f1b1\" id=\"u2ee8f1b1\">]</span></li></ul><p data-lake-id=\"u23900547\" id=\"u23900547\"><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u83ae41ee\" id=\"u83ae41ee\">总结：</span></strong><span data-lake-id=\"u69c4267c\" id=\"u69c4267c\"> 对于产品设计师而言，当下的核心策略是：</span><strong><span data-lake-id=\"u8a1c473d\" id=\"u8a1c473d\">放下对工具（仅限Figma）和流程（严格的双钻模型）的执念，拥抱代码和模型，从“图纸绘制者”转型为“最后一步的构建者”和“产品愿景的掌舵人”。</span></strong></p>"}
